                "content": "<P>You should discuss the situation with your MLRO who can help you to manage the tipping off risk.</P><P><BR>Offering to delay the meeting could lead to a conversation with the customer where it may be difficult to avoid tipping them off. It is not your role to conduct an investigation and such lines of questioning may put you at risk of tipping off. Telling your customer that you can have no further contact until the police investigation is concluded will directly tip him off.</P>",
